The article is a statement from the former National Security Advisor, in which he expresses his pride in the role played by the National Security Council (NSC) in restoring America's strategic confidence under President Donald J. Trump. The NSC helped set a strategic direction for the United States, focusing on protecting the American people, promoting prosperity, preserving peace through strength, and advancing American influence. Some of the accomplishments mentioned include a new approach to North Korea, addressing China's economic aggression, imposing costs on Russia for its destabilizing actions, countering Iran's proxy war and support for terrorist groups, defeating ISIS, holding Pakistan accountable, and strengthening NATO alliances. The former National Security Advisor also expresses his appreciation for the dedicated NSC staff and wishes success to his successor, Ambassador John Bolton.